race.comment: TIERRA (12) is putting together some solid results. Finished second at Tatura two starts back then got the job done by 1.7L as the public elect over 2010m at Kilmore. Meeting a tougher field but has weight relief and is capable of testing her rivals. BURLINGTON GATE (5) switched to the Hayes yard and didn't have the nest of it first-up over a mile. She was expected to need it anyway. The longer trip suits and presenting fitter she's the threat. BOGUES (3) is a local on resumption. May find the above pair too nippy, but he's racing at home and is likely to be finishing hard. REBADGE (7) resumes and has jumped out well three times at Flemington.Egan sticks from those and he maps well. He will be around the mark.
